---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import { webForgeUrl } from '../../data/products';
---
<DocsLayout
  title="Forge desktop (retired)"
  eyebrow="Products"
  description="The desktop app has been retired — use Forge in your browser or the agentkitforge CLI."
>
  <div class="docs-note">
    <strong>The AgentKitForge desktop app has been retired.</strong> Everything it did is
    now covered by <a href={webForgeUrl}>Forge in your browser</a> and the
    <a href="/docs/cli/">agentkitforge CLI</a>.
  </div>

  <p>
    Build, validate, package, export, import, and run Agent Kits — plus Market submit/import
    — all work from <a href="/docs/web-forge/">Forge (web)</a>. For local-first, headless, or
    scripted workflows with no account, use the <a href="/docs/cli/">CLI</a>. Both share the
    same <code>@agentkitforge/core</code> engine, so results are identical everywhere.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
